1. What is an API?

API = Application Programming Interface
It allows your program to get data from websites/services.

Example:

Weather data 🌦️
Stock prices 📈
Maps 

2. Install requests Library
pip install requests

3. Simple API Program (Get Data)
Program
import requests

url = "https://api.github.com"

response = requests.get(url)

print(response.status_code)
Output
200

200 means request successful

4. Get JSON Data from API
Program
import requests

url = "https://api.github.com"

response = requests.get(url)

data = response.json()

print(data)
Output (shortened)
{'current_user_url': 'https://api.github.com/user', ...}

5. Weather API Example 🌦️
Program
import requests

city = input("Enter city: ")

url = f"https://wttr.in/{city}?format=3"

response = requests.get(url)

print(response.text)
Input
Enter city: Bangalore
Output (example)
Bangalore: +28°C

6. Random Joke API 
Program
import requests

url = "https://official-joke-api.appspot.com/random_joke"

response = requests.get(url)

data = response.json()

print(data["setup"])
print(data["punchline"])
Output (example)
Why did the computer go to the doctor?
Because it had a virus!

7. Check API Status
import requests

response = requests.get("https://api.github.com")

if response.status_code == 200:
    print("Success")
else:
    print("Failed")
Output
Success
